thread.title: Egypt's next parliament unlikely to challenge Sisi

title: Egypt's next parliament unlikely to challenge Sisi
text:
Cairo - Egyptians are preparing to go to the polls in the second parliamentary elections since dictator Hosni Mubarak was toppled in a 2011 revolution. But with President Abdel-Fattah al-Sisi firmly in control, there is little excitement about elections many expect to result in a fractured but loyalist parliament.
The Cairo headquarters of Egypt's former ruling party, torched during the 2011 uprising against Hosni Mubarak, is being demolished just as the country prepares for its second parliamentary elections since the dictator was toppled.
The 14-storey burned-out hulk, a constant reminder of the revolt over the past four years, has been levelled halfway to the ground.
But Egypt now has a new strongman.
